{"id":"1007.2599","submitter":"Katiuscia Cassemiro","authors":"Katiuscia N. Cassemiro, Kaisa Laiho, and Christine Silberhorn","title":"Accessing the purity of a single photon by the width of the\n  Hong-Ou-Mandel interference","comments":"Extended version, 16 pages, 9 figures","journal-ref":"New J. Phys. 12 113052 (2010)","doi":"10.1088/1367-2630/12/11/113052","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We demonstrate a method to determine the spectral purity of single photons.\nThe technique is based on the Hong-Ou-Mandel (HOM) interference between a\nsingle photon state and a suitably prepared coherent field. We show that the\ntemporal width of the HOM dip is not only related to reciprocal of the spectral\nwidth but also to the underlying quantum coherence. Therefore, by measuring the\nwidth of both the HOM dip and the spectrum one can directly quantify the degree\nof spectral purity. The distinct advantage of our proposal is that it obviates\nthe need for perfect mode matching, since it does not rely on the visibility of\nthe interference. Our method is particularly useful for characterizing the\npurity of heralded single photon states.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 15 Jul 2010 15:57:40 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 6 Oct 2010 20:29:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2010-12-07"}
